#. <section class="sutta" id="sn9.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.11:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.11:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga"
msgstr "1. In the Woods"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 11. Akusalavitakkasutta → ayonisosuttaṃ (bj) | ayonisomanasikārasuttaṃ (s1-3, pts2) | ayoniso (vitakkitā) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn9.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Akusalavitakkasutta"
msgstr "11. Unskillful Thoughts"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.437"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.11:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ aññataro bhikkhu kosalesu viharati aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe."
msgstr ""
"At one time one of the mendicants was staying in the land of the Kosalans in "
"a certain forest grove."

msgctxt "sn9.11:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena so bhikkhu divāvihāragato pāpake akusale vitakke "
"vitakketi, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Now at that time that mendicant, during their day’s meditation, was thinking "
"bad, unskillful thoughts, that is:"

msgctxt "sn9.11:1.3"
msgid "kāmavitakkaṃ, byāpādavitakkaṃ, vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ."
msgstr "sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts."

msgctxt "sn9.11:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho yā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā tassa bhikkhuno anukampikā "
"atthakāmā taṃ bhikkhuṃ saṃvejetukāmā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"The deity haunting that forest had compassion for that mendicant, and wanted "
"what’s best for them. So they approached that mendicant wanting to stir them "
"up, and addressed them in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.11:2.1"
msgid "“Ayoniso manasikārā,"
msgstr "“Because of improper attention,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.11:2.2"
msgid "so vitakkehi khajjasi;"
msgstr "you’re consumed by your thoughts."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Ayoniso → ayoniṃ (pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn9.11:2.3"
msgid "Ayoniso paṭinissajja,"
msgstr "When you’ve given up irrationality,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.11:2.4"
msgid "yoniso anucintaya."
msgstr "make sure your thoughts are rational."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.11:3.1"
msgid "Satthāraṃ dhammamārabbha,"
msgstr "Thinking about the Teacher, the teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.11:3.2"
msgid "saṅghaṃ sīlāni attano;"
msgstr "the Saṅgha, and your own ethics,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.11:3.3"
msgid "Adhigacchasi pāmojjaṃ,"
msgstr "you’ll find gladness,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.11:3.4"
msgid "pītisukhamasaṃsayaṃ;"
msgstr "and rapture and bliss as well, no doubt."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.11:3.5"
msgid "Tato pāmojjabahulo,"
msgstr "And when you’re full of joy,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.11:3.6"
msgid "dukkhassantaṃ karissasī”ti."
msgstr "you’ll make an end to suffering.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.11:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu tāya devatāya saṃvejito saṃvegamāpādīti."
msgstr ""
"Impelled by that deity, that mendicant was filled with a sense of urgency."
